    <h3 class="section-title">XII. GENERAL PHYSICAL EXAMINATION</h3>
    <div class="sub-list">
      <p><strong>General Appearance:</strong> [Alert, active, playful /
        Irritable, lethargic, drowsy, comatose / Well-nourished, undernourished,
        obese / In distress (respiratory, pain) / Comfortable]</p>
      <p><strong>Built:</strong> [Average/Thin/Obese]
        &Acirc;&nbsp;&Acirc;&nbsp;&Acirc;&nbsp;&Acirc;&nbsp; <strong>Nourishment:</strong>
        [Good/Fair/Poor]</p>
      <p><strong>Level of Consciousness (GCS if applicable):</strong> [Score,
        E_V_M_]</p>
      <p><strong>Cooperation:</strong> [Cooperative/Uncooperative]</p>
      <p><strong>Anthropometry:</strong> </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Weight: [kg] (<span class="detail-prompt">Percentile: [...])</span></li>
        <li>Height/Length: [cm] (<span class="detail-prompt">Percentile: [...])</span></li>
        <li>Head Circumference (if &lt;3 years): [cm] (<span class="detail-prompt">Percentile:
            [...])</span></li>
        <li>Mid-Upper Arm Circumference (MUAC, if applicable): [cm]</li>
        <li>BMI (if applicable): [kg/m<sup>2</sup>] (<span class="detail-prompt">Percentile:
            [...])</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Vital Signs:</strong> </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Temperature: [...&Acirc;&deg;C/&Acirc;&deg;F] (<span class="detail-prompt">Site:
            Axillary/Oral/Rectal)</span></li>
        <li>Pulse Rate: [.../min] (<span class="detail-prompt">Rhythm:
            Regular/Irregular; <span class="detail-prompt">Volume: Good/Low; <span

                class="detail-prompt">Character: [...]; <span class="detail-prompt">Peripheral
                  pulses: Palpable/Equal)</span></span></span></span></li>
        <li>Respiratory Rate: [.../min] (<span class="detail-prompt">Rhythm:
            Regular/Irregular; <span class="detail-prompt">Type:
              Abdominal/Thoracoabdominal)</span></span></li>
        <li>Blood Pressure: [.../... mmHg] (<span class="detail-prompt">Limb:
            Right/Left Arm/Leg; <span class="detail-prompt">Cuff size: [...])</span></span></li>
        <li>SpO<sub>2</sub>: [...% on room air / with O<sub>2</sub> at ...L/min]</li>
        <li>Capillary Refill Time (CRT): [&lt;3 sec / &gt;3 sec]</li>
        <li>Pain Score (e.g., FLACC, Wong-Baker FACES, Numeric): [...]</li>
      </ul>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>General Survey:</strong> </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Pallor: [Present/Absent]</li>
        <li>Icterus: [Present/Absent]</li>
        <li>Cyanosis: [Central/Peripheral/Absent]</li>
        <li>Clubbing: [Present (Grade)/Absent]</li>
        <li>Koilonychia: [Present/Absent]</li>
        <li>Edema: [Pitting/Non-pitting, Site, Extent]</li>
        <li>Dehydration: [Signs - sunken eyes, dry tongue, skin turgor, sunken
          fontanelle if applicable; Grade - Mild/Moderate/Severe/None]</li>
        <li>Lymphadenopathy: [Site, size, consistency, tenderness, mobility,
          overlying skin changes]</li>
        <li>Skin: [Color, texture, turgor, rashes, lesions, scars,
          neurocutaneous markers (e.g., ash-leaf spots,
          caf&Atilde;&copy;-au-lait spots, neurofibromas, port-wine stain)]</li>
        <li>Hair &amp; Nails: [Texture, distribution, abnormalities]</li>
        <li>Head &amp; Face: [Shape, size, fontanelles (if open - size,
          tension), sutures, dysmorphic features, facies]</li>
        <li>Eyes: [Conjunctiva, sclera, pupils (size, symmetry, reaction to
          light), extraocular movements, strabismus, discharge]</li>
        <li>Ears: [External ear, canals, tympanic membranes (otoscope if
          needed), discharge, tenderness]</li>
        <li>Nose: [Patency, discharge, septum, sinuses (tenderness if older
          child)]</li>
        <li>Mouth &amp; Throat: [Lips, oral mucosa, tongue, teeth (dentition,
          caries), gums, tonsils, pharynx, palate, cry (if infant)]</li>
        <li>Neck: [Symmetry, swelling, masses, thyroid, range of motion, JVP (if
          assessable), nuchal rigidity]</li>
        <li>Obvious swellings/deformities: [Describe]</li>
      </ul>
      <p></p>
    </div>
    <h3 class="section-title">XIII. SYSTEMIC EXAMINATION</h3>
    <div class="sub-list">
      <h4>A. RESPIRATORY SYSTEM</h4>
      <p><strong>Inspection:</strong> [Shape of chest, symmetry of movements,
        respiratory rate, rhythm, type of breathing, use of accessory muscles,
        intercostal/subcostal retractions, nasal flaring, tracheal position,
        scars, dilated veins]</p>
      <p><strong>Palpation:</strong> [Chest expansion, vocal fremitus/tactile
        fremitus, tenderness, rib cage integrity, apical impulse position]</p>
      <p><strong>Percussion:</strong> [Resonant/Dull/Hyperresonant over all lung
        fields, comparing sides]</p>
      <p><strong>Auscultation:</strong> [Breath sounds - character
        (vesicular/bronchial), intensity, equality; Adventitious sounds -
        wheezes, rales/crackles, rhonchi, pleural rub; Vocal resonance]</p>
      <h4>B. CARDIOVASCULAR SYSTEM</h4>
      <p><strong>Pulse:</strong> (Already noted in vitals, re-evaluate for
        specific cardiac features if needed)</p>
      <p><strong>Blood Pressure:</strong> (Already noted, consider 4-limb BP if
        indicated)</p>
      <p><strong>JVP:</strong> [If assessable]</p>
      <p><strong>Precordial Examination:</strong> </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Inspection: [Visible pulsations, scars, chest deformity]</li>
        <li>Palpation: [Apical impulse - location (ICS, MCL), character;
          Thrills, heaves, palpable heart sounds]</li>
        <li>Auscultation: [Heart sounds - S1, S2 (splitting, intensity); Added
          sounds - S3, S4, murmurs (timing, location, radiation, intensity,
          pitch, quality), clicks, rubs]</li>
      </ul>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Peripheral Signs:</strong> [Clubbing, cyanosis, edema, splinter
        hemorrhages, Janeway lesions, Osler's nodes, peripheral pulses -
        character, equality]</p>
      <h4>C. GASTROINTESTINAL SYSTEM (ABDOMEN)</h4>
      <p><strong>Inspection:</strong> [Shape, contour (flat/scaphoid/distended),
        symmetry, umbilicus (position, everted/inverted, discharge), skin
        (scars, striae, dilated veins), visible peristalsis, movements with
        respiration]</p>
      <p><strong>Auscultation:</strong> [Bowel sounds - present/absent,
        character (normoactive/hyperactive/hypoactive); Bruits]</p>
      <p><strong>Palpation:</strong> </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Superficial: [Tenderness (site, nature), guarding, rigidity,
          superficial masses]</li>
        <li>Deep: [Organomegaly - Liver (span, consistency, surface, edge,
          tenderness), Spleen (palpable/not, size, consistency), Kidneys
          (ballotable/not); Deep masses (site, size, shape, consistency,
          mobility, tenderness)]</li>
        <li>Hernial orifices: [Intact/hernia present]</li>
      </ul>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Percussion:</strong> [Tympanitic/Dull over abdomen, liver span,
        splenic dullness, shifting dullness/fluid thrill (if ascites suspected)]</p>
      <p><strong>Digital Rectal Examination (DRE):</strong> [If indicated -
        sphincter tone, masses, tenderness, stool characteristics]</p>
      <p><strong>Genitalia (External):</strong> [If indicated/relevant - Tanner
        staging for adolescents, abnormalities, discharge, inflammation]</p>
      <h4>D. CENTRAL NERVOUS SYSTEM</h4>
      <p><strong>Higher Intellectual Functions (Age-appropriate):</strong> </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Consciousness: [Alert/Drowsy/Stuporous/Comatose; GCS if applicable]</li>
        <li>Orientation: [Time, place, person (age-appropriate)]</li>
        <li>Memory: [Immediate, recent, remote (age-appropriate assessment)]</li>
        <li>Speech: [Fluency, comprehension, naming, repetition, dysarthria,
          aphasia (age-appropriate)]</li>
        <li>Behavior &amp; Mood: [Appropriate/Inappropriate, irritable,
          withdrawn, hyperactive]</li>
        <li>General Intelligence/Cognition: [Impression based on interaction and
          age]</li>
      </ol>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Cranial Nerves (I-XII):</strong> <span class="detail-prompt">(Detailed
          examination as indicated) </span></p>
      <ol>
        <li>I (Olfactory): [Sense of smell - if testable]</li>
        <li>II (Optic): [Visual acuity, visual fields, fundoscopy (if
          indicated)]</li>
        <li>III, IV, VI (Oculomotor, Trochlear, Abducens): [Pupil size/reaction,
          ptosis, eye movements, nystagmus, diplopia]</li>
        <li>V (Trigeminal): [Facial sensation, corneal reflex, muscles of
          mastication]</li>
        <li>VII (Facial): [Facial symmetry (at rest, on movement - smile, frown,
          eye closure), taste (anterior 2/3)]</li>
        <li>VIII (Vestibulocochlear): [Hearing (gross, Rinne's, Weber's - if
          age-appropriate), vertigo, nystagmus]</li>
        <li>IX, X (Glossopharyngeal, Vagus): [Gag reflex, palate movement, voice
          quality, swallowing]</li>
        <li>XI (Accessory): [Shoulder shrug, head turning against resistance]</li>
        <li>XII (Hypoglossal): [Tongue protrusion, movements, fasciculations,
          wasting]</li>
      </ol>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Motor System:</strong> </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Nutrition/Bulk of Muscles: [Normal/Wasting/Hypertrophy -
          distribution]</li>
        <li>Tone: [Normal/Hypotonia/Hypertonia (Spasticity/Rigidity) -
          distribution]</li>
        <li>Power (MRC Scale 0-5): [Assess major muscle groups in all four
          limbs, proximal/distal]</li>
        <li>Involuntary Movements: [Tremors, chorea, athetosis, dystonia,
          myoclonus, fasciculations - describe]</li>
        <li>Coordination: [Finger-nose test, heel-shin test, rapid alternating
          movements, Romberg's test (age-appropriate)]</li>
        <li>Gait: [Normal/Abnormal - describe type (e.g., ataxic, spastic,
          waddling, hemiplegic)]</li>
      </ol>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Sensory System:</strong> <span class="detail-prompt">(If
          cooperative and indicated) </span></p>
      <ol>
        <li>Superficial Sensation: [Touch, pain, temperature]</li>
        <li>Deep Sensation: [Joint position sense, vibration sense]</li>
        <li>Cortical Sensation: [Stereognosis, graphesthesia, two-point
          <p></p>
          <p><strong>Reflexes:</strong> </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Superficial Reflexes:
              <ol>
                <li>Abdominal</li>
                <li>Cremasteric</li>
                <li>Plantar (Babinski sign)</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Deep Tendon Reflexes (DTRs):
              <ol>
                <li>Biceps</li>
                <li>Triceps</li>
                <li>Supinator</li>
                <li>Knee</li>
                <li>Ankle - Grade 0 to 4+, symmetry</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Clonus:
              <ol>
                <li>Ankle</li>
                <li>Patellar - Present/Absent</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Primitive Reflexes (if infant):
              <ol>
                <li>Moro</li>
                <li>Grasp</li>
                <li>Rooting</li>
                <li>Sucking</li>
                <li>ATNR - Present/Absent, appropriate for age</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p></p>
          <p><strong>Signs of Meningeal Irritation:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Nuchal rigidity</li>
            <li>Kernig's sign</li>
            <li>Brudzinski's sign</li>
          </ol>
          <p><strong>Skull &amp; Spine:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Palpate for deformities</li>
            <li>Tenderness</li>
            <li>Check for spinal curvature</li>
          </ol>
          <h4>E. OTHER SYSTEMS</h4>
          <p class="detail-prompt">(Brief examination of other systems like
            Endocrine, Hematological as relevant to the case)</p>
          <p>[Details]</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <h3 class="section-title">XIV. SEXUAL HISTORY (FOR ADOLESCENTS / AS
      INDICATED)</h3>
    <div class="sub-list">
      <p>Are you sexually active? [Yes/No]</p>
      <p>If yes: </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Age of first sexual intercourse: [...]</li>
        <li>Number of partners (lifetime, last 3/6/12 months): [...]</li>
        <li>Gender(s) of partners / Sexual orientation: [...]</li>
        <li>Types of sexual contact:
          <ol>
            <li>Oral</li>
            <li>Vaginal</li>
            <li>Anal - insertive/receptive</li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>Use of barrier contraception (condoms, dental dams):
          <ol>
            <li>Always</li>
            <li>Sometimes</li>
            <li>Never</li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>Other methods of contraception: [Details]</li>
        <li>History of STIs: [Previous diagnosis, treatment]</li>
        <li>Any concerns about sexual health: [Details]</li>
        <li>History of sexual abuse or non-consensual contact: [Handle with
          sensitivity, if disclosed]</li>
      </ol>
      <p></p>
    </div>
    <h3 class="section-title">XV. SUMMARY OF HISTORY AND EXAMINATION</h3>
    <p>[A concise summary of the pertinent positive and negative findings from
      the history and physical examination. e.g., "Master/Miss X, a Y-year-old
      child, presented with (chief complaints) for (duration). History is
      significant for... Examination revealed..."]</p>
    <h3 class="section-title">XVI. PROVISIONAL DIAGNOSIS</h3>
    <p>[Most likely diagnosis based on history and examination]</p>
    <h3 class="section-title">XVII. DIFFERENTIAL DIAGNOSES</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>[Differential 1]</li>
      <li>[Differential 2]</li>
      <li>[Differential 3]</li>
    </ol>
    <h3 class="section-title">XVIII. INVESTIGATIONS</h3>
    <p class="detail-prompt">(Plan investigations to confirm diagnosis, rule out
      differentials, and assess severity/complications. Categorize as Baseline,
      Specific, etc.)</p>
    <div class="sub-list">
      <p><strong>Baseline Investigations:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>Complete Blood Count (CBC) with peripheral smear</li>
        <li>Erythrocyte Sedimentation Rate (ESR) / C-Reactive Protein (CRP)</li>
        <li>Urinalysis</li>
        <li>Blood glucose</li>
      </ol>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Specific Investigations:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>Blood culture</li>
        <li>Throat swab</li>
        <li>Stool culture</li>
        <li>Chest X-ray</li>
        <li>Ultrasound abdomen</li>
        <li>Lumbar puncture and CSF analysis</li>
        <li>Specific antibody tests</li>
        <li>PCR</li>
      </ol>
      <p></p>
      <p><strong>Other Investigations (as indicated):</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>[Details]</li>
      </ol>
      <p></p>
    </div>
    <h3 class="section-title">XIX. MANAGEMENT PLAN</h3>
    <div class="sub-list">
      <p><strong>Immediate Management (if any, e.g., in ER):</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>[Details]</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Specific Treatment (Pharmacological):</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>Drug name</li>
        <li>Dose</li>
        <li>Route</li>
        <li>Frequency</li>
        <li>Duration</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Supportive Treatment (Non-Pharmacological):</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>IV fluids</li>
        <li>Oxygen</li>
        <li>Nutritional support</li>
        <li>Physiotherapy</li>
        <li>Counseling</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Monitoring:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>Parameters to monitor</li>
        <li>Frequency</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Patient/Parent Education &amp; Counseling:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>Regarding illness</li>
        <li>Treatment</li>
        <li>Prognosis</li>
        <li>Prevention</li>
        <li>Red flag signs</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Referral (if any):</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>To specialist/department</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Follow-up Plan:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>When</li>
        <li>Where</li>
        <li>What to assess</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

